    "Hence, these items in the scale measured skills, knowledge, intentions, benefits of the tools, and their concerns about policies in using them.",
    "The ten items on perceptions have Cronbach's Alpha reliability coefficient of 0.85, which indicates a good internal consistency for the scale (George & Mallery 2003).",
    "Open-ended questions were framed to allow participants to elaborate further and explain their concerns and perceived benefits of using the said tools.",
    "Questions about educators' practices in using ChatGPT and other ADWTs consist of whether or not they have used the applications, frequency of use, purposes, tasks, and how these tools are incorporated into their teaching and research.",
    "Participants were likewise interrogated if they thought the use of these tools should be regulated or completely banned from coursework and research-related tasks."
  ],
